@startuml
title Use Case: Generate Report

actor "Officer" as O
actor "Supervisor" as S
actor "Records Clerk" as RC
actor "Prosecutor" as P

usecase "Generate Report" as UC

O --> UC : creates/edits report
S --> UC : reviews/approves report
RC --> UC : files/distributes report
P --> UC : receives/uses report

UC .> (Select Report Template) : include
UC .> (Enter Incident Details) : include
UC .> (Add Involved Persons) : include
UC .> (Attach Evidence References) : include
UC .> (Sign Electronically) : include

UC <.. (Generate Statistical Analysis) : extend <<if aggregate data needed>>
UC <.. (Produce Public Version) : extend <<if public release required>>
UC <.. (Create Court Package) : extend <<if for legal proceedings>>
UC <.. (Export to External System) : extend <<if inter-agency sharing>>

note right of UC
  ID: UC-006
  Priority: Medium
  Frequency: Multiple daily per officer
  Preconditions: Incident occurred, officer involved
  Postconditions: Report created, approved, filed
  Main Success: Accurate, complete, timely documentation
end note

rectangle "Report Types" {
  (Incident Report) as RT1
  (Arrest Report) as RT2
  (Traffic Accident) as RT3
  (Use of Force) as RT4
  (Evidence Report) as RT5

  RT1 -[hidden] RT2
  RT2 -[hidden] RT3
  RT3 -[hidden] RT4
  RT4 -[hidden] RT5
}

UC --> RT1 : includes
UC --> RT2 : includes
UC --> RT3 : includes
UC --> RT4 : includes
UC --> RT5 : includes
@enduml
